Returns a new function that postpones execution until `delay` ms have elapsed since the last call.

```js
const debounce = (fn, delay) => {
  let timer;
  return (...args) => {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn(...args), delay);
  };
};

// Usage --------------------------
const log = msg => console.log(msg);
const smartLog = debounce(log, 300);

smartLog('Hi!');   // nothing yet
setTimeout(() => smartLog('Debounce!'), 100);  // prints "Debounce!" ~300 ms after the second call
```
